In this article, Vice President Pence and State Counselor Aung San Suu Kyi of Burma (also known as Myanmar) discuss the partnership between the United States and Burma. Pence expresses the desire for a prosperous and peaceful civil society in Burma with a free and independent press. He also mentions the importance of hearing about the progress of democratic reforms in Burma and the efforts to address the Rohingya crisis. Pence emphasizes the need for accountability for the violence against the Rohingya and the possibility of their voluntary return. He also mentions the concern over the arrest and jailing of two journalists in Burma. State Counselor Aung San Suu Kyi expresses the importance of exchanging views and understanding each other better. She welcomes support to make Burma a safer and more prosperous place for everyone.